16
00:01:03,663 --> 00:01:05,098
<i>however crazy they seem</i>

17
00:01:05,131 --> 00:01:08,568
<i>And I won't stop 'til I</i>
<i>get there, you will see</i>

18
00:01:08,601 --> 00:01:09,736
<i>You're all I need</i>

19
00:01:09,769 --> 00:01:11,905
<i>to have the strength to believe</i>

20
00:01:11,938 --> 00:01:18,011
<i>Believe in Wonderland!</i>

21
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:22,148
<i>I'm gonna follow my dreams,</i>

22
00:01:22,148 --> 00:01:23,817
<i>however crazy they seem</i>

23
00:01:23,817 --> 00:01:25,452
<i>I'm gonna share them with you,</i>

24
00:01:25,485 --> 00:01:26,986
<i>a love so true</i>

25
00:01:26,986 --> 00:01:30,523
<i>You're all I want,</i>
<i>together we can move on</i>

26
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:32,992
<i>Live how we want to!</i>

27
00:01:32,992 --> 00:01:34,627
<i>There is no limit to us,</i>

28
00:01:34,661 --> 00:01:36,096
<i>we have the power of love</i>

29
00:01:36,129 --> 00:01:39,466
<i>And we don't wanna</i>
<i>live ordinary lives</i>

30
00:01:39,499 --> 00:01:42,869
<i>We have the chance</i>
<i>to live in paradise</i>

31
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:48,041
<i>Believe in Wonderland!♪</i>

32
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:02,489
[LUFFY]
My hat!

33
00:02:02,489 --> 00:02:04,390
Wait!

34
00:02:07,060 --> 00:02:09,295
[LUFFY]
Stop hat!

35
00:02:11,498 --> 00:02:13,333
[LUFFY]
Good! My hat.

36
00:02:17,003 --> 00:02:21,307
[LUFFY] So this is what the King
of the Pirates saw when he died.

37
00:02:22,475 --> 00:02:25,211
[laughs]

38
00:02:25,245 --> 00:02:27,347
[BUGGY] Ugh! I hate
that damn Straw Hat

39
00:02:27,347 --> 00:02:28,882
and I want to crush
him like a bug

40
00:02:28,915 --> 00:02:31,518
the next time I see
his ugly face.

41
00:02:35,188 --> 00:02:37,357
So he finally showed up.

42
00:02:37,390 --> 00:02:39,592
It took him long enough.

43
00:02:39,659 --> 00:02:41,561
[TASHIGI]
Captain Smoker!

44
00:02:41,594 --> 00:02:43,429
Is there something wrong?

45
00:02:43,496 --> 00:02:45,598
Come with me, Tashigi.

46
00:02:45,665 --> 00:02:46,933
Sir!

47
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:51,004
[thunder rumbles]

48
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:55,341
[LUFFY]
"Buggy's Revenge!

49
00:02:55,375 --> 00:02:59,179
The Man Who Smiles On
the Execution Platform!"

50
00:03:01,447 --> 00:03:04,017
[TOWNSMAN 7] Whoa! Someone's
on the execution platform!

51
00:03:04,050 --> 00:03:06,553
[TOWNSMAN 8]
Who the heck is that?

52
00:03:06,586 --> 00:03:09,622
That old man said this is the
place where it all happened.

53
00:03:09,689 --> 00:03:12,091
Twenty‐two years ago,
the King of the Pirates

54
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:14,427
was executed right here.

55
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:17,630
[POLICE CAPTAIN]
Hey! You! Up there!

56
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:23,203
[POLICE CAPTAIN]
Get down from there immediately!

57
00:03:23,236 --> 00:03:24,470
[LUFFY]
But why?

58
00:03:24,537 --> 00:03:26,739
You are standing on
an execution platform

59
00:03:26,739 --> 00:03:29,075
that belongs to the
World Government!

60
00:03:29,075 --> 00:03:31,411
Now get down from
there right now!

61
00:03:31,444 --> 00:03:32,579
Fine.

62
00:03:32,612 --> 00:03:35,215
I'll come down but first you
gotta say the magic word.

63
00:03:35,248 --> 00:03:36,382
And smile too.

64
00:03:36,416 --> 00:03:37,250
I'm not playing!

65
00:03:37,283 --> 00:03:40,220
I'll arrest you if
you don't come down!

66
00:03:43,556 --> 00:03:47,093
[ALVIDA] Now's not the
time for such trifles.

67
00:03:47,093 --> 00:03:52,065
Long time no see, Luffy.
I've been looking for you.

68
00:03:57,170 --> 00:03:57,971
[LUFFY]
Huh?

69
00:03:58,004 --> 00:03:59,239
Now that's just rude.

70
00:03:59,272 --> 00:04:01,641
Do you mean to tell me
that you, of all people,

71
00:04:01,674 --> 00:04:03,643
have forgotten my face?

72
00:04:03,676 --> 00:04:05,645
Wow, she's absolutely gorgeous!

73
00:04:05,678 --> 00:04:06,779
Oh, wow.

74
00:04:06,779 --> 00:04:08,615
I've never seen
such pure beauty!

75
00:04:08,648 --> 00:04:11,517
Her skin looks so
deliciously soft!

76
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:14,687
Forgot? I'm pretty sure
we haven't ever met.

77
00:04:14,754 --> 00:04:16,289
Who are you?

78
00:04:16,322 --> 00:04:18,291
[ALVIDA]
I'll never forget you.

79
00:04:18,291 --> 00:04:21,194
You were the first man
who ever truly struck me.

80
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:23,296
[LUFFY]
What? I never hit you!

81
00:04:23,296 --> 00:04:27,133
[CROWD chattering]

82
00:04:27,133 --> 00:04:31,204
[ALVIDA] When you struck me
with your passionate fist...

83
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:33,539
[LUFFY]
Gum‐Gum!

84
00:04:33,606 --> 00:04:35,441
Pistol!

85
00:04:43,483 --> 00:04:45,518
It felt good.

86
00:04:48,621 --> 00:04:49,722
Listen up, boys.

87
00:04:49,789 --> 00:04:52,625
What would all of you say
is the most beautiful sight

88
00:04:52,659 --> 00:04:54,661
in the whole East Blue?

89
00:04:54,694 --> 00:04:56,529
[CROWD]
That would be you!

90
00:04:56,562 --> 00:04:57,797
[ALVIDA]
That's correct.

91
00:04:57,830 --> 00:04:59,732
I am quite breathtaking,
aren't I?

92
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:02,235
There isn't a man alive
who wouldn't crumble

93
00:05:02,302 --> 00:05:04,404
before my beauty.

94
00:05:04,470 --> 00:05:06,739
But I prefer strong men.

95
00:05:06,806 --> 00:05:11,377
Like you. I'm going to make
you all mine, Luffy. Just wait.

96
00:05:11,411 --> 00:05:12,845
Aw, gross! No way.

97
00:05:12,845 --> 00:05:14,414
Just who the heck are you?!

98
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:17,083
[ALVIDA] You still haven't
figured it out?!

99
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:18,318
[ASST. POLICE CAPTAIN]
This is the police!

100
00:05:18,351 --> 00:05:20,653
Put your weapon down
and come quietly!

101
00:05:20,687 --> 00:05:25,191
I am placing you under arrest
for assaulting a police captain!

102
00:05:25,191 --> 00:05:27,727
As for you up there!
Get off that platform!

103
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:31,197
Hold on. Who did you
say you were arresting?

104
00:05:31,197 --> 00:05:33,666
We're arresting you!

105
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:37,337
[ALVIDA] Are you really
going to arrest me?

106
00:05:38,271 --> 00:05:41,107
[chuckles]

107
00:05:41,174 --> 00:05:42,709
We've got a big
problem here, sir.

108
00:05:42,742 --> 00:05:44,077
She's too beautiful!

109
00:05:44,110 --> 00:05:46,546
I really don't give
a damn! Arrest her!

110
00:05:46,546 --> 00:05:47,714
[OFFICER A]
Do we have to?

111
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:49,382
[OFFICER B] Can't we just
stand here and look at her?

112
00:05:49,415 --> 00:05:51,784
[BUGGY]
Surprise!

113
00:05:53,186 --> 00:05:54,687
[OFFICER B]
A terrorist bombing!

114
00:05:54,721 --> 00:05:56,789
[TOWNSMAN 8]
Watch out, miss!

115
00:05:59,359 --> 00:06:00,560
Did that just‐‐?

116
00:06:00,593 --> 00:06:02,595
It slipped right past her!

117
00:06:02,628 --> 00:06:04,797
Oh man. That's weird!

118
00:06:04,864 --> 00:06:07,233
[BUGGY laughing]

119
00:06:07,266 --> 00:06:09,802
That little stunt was
dangerous, you know?

120
00:06:09,869 --> 00:06:11,604
[BUGGY]
I'm flashily sorry.

121
00:06:11,637 --> 00:06:14,207
But your smooth skin
is unharmed, of course,

122
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:18,644
so there's no need for
trouble, fairest Alvida.

123
00:06:18,711 --> 00:06:20,446
[chuckles]

124
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:22,315
Alvida?

125
00:06:24,751 --> 00:06:26,319
[LUFFY]
I don't see Alvida.

126
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:29,389
Don't be so dense,
you nimwit! I'm Alvida!

127
00:06:29,422 --> 00:06:33,593
Are you sure? 'Cause I
don't think you're her.

128
00:06:33,626 --> 00:06:37,563
I guess I really did change
after eating the fruit called...

129
00:06:39,432 --> 00:06:41,467
...Smooth‐Smooth Fruit.

130
00:06:41,501 --> 00:06:46,339
No attack can hurt my skin
because it slides right off.

131
00:06:46,406 --> 00:06:49,175
Unfortunately, a lowly fruit
couldn't improve upon

132
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:51,744
my already stunning good looks.

133
00:06:51,778 --> 00:06:53,613
One big change you
may have noticed

134
00:06:53,646 --> 00:06:55,581
was that I
lost my freckles.

135
00:06:55,615 --> 00:06:58,284
[LUFFY]
Sure, that must be it.

136
00:06:58,284 --> 00:07:00,153
After becoming a
whole new person,

137
00:07:00,186 --> 00:07:02,422
I decided to join
forces with someone

138
00:07:02,455 --> 00:07:04,490
who shared my goal
of finding you.

139
00:07:04,524 --> 00:07:10,530
[BUGGY laughing]

140
00:07:12,799 --> 00:07:14,634
Now that I've flashily
made my entrance,

141
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:18,504
behold the real
star of this show.

142
00:07:18,538 --> 00:07:20,306
Monkey D. Luffy!

143
00:07:20,306 --> 00:07:22,542
Ever since the day
you sent me flying,

144
00:07:22,608 --> 00:07:25,778
I've been obsessed with
exacting my revenge on you.

145
00:07:25,812 --> 00:07:29,649
That alone led me to finally
finding my crew!

146
00:07:29,682 --> 00:07:31,484
My travels are an epic saga.

147
00:07:31,484 --> 00:07:33,219
I went through hell,
found friendship,

148
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:34,687
I even lost parts of my body.

149
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:37,657
I call this tale:
"Tiny Buggy's Great Adventure"!

150
00:07:37,657 --> 00:07:38,891
The first thing that
happened was‐‐

151
00:07:38,958 --> 00:07:41,327
Why the hell am I
telling you a story?!

152
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:44,497
Don't know. Now...
what was your name again?

153
00:07:44,497 --> 00:07:47,633
Boggy? Boogie? Behie? Baggy?

154
00:07:47,667 --> 00:07:50,536
Ah! I know! It's Buffoon!

155
00:07:52,972 --> 00:07:55,908
Buffoon?! You got a lot
of nerve you rubber bastard!

156
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:59,512
And now Buggy the Clown is
gonna make you pay for that!

157
00:07:59,545 --> 00:08:01,747
Hey, that's Buggy the Clown!

158
00:08:01,814 --> 00:08:03,249
Pirates!

159
00:08:03,316 --> 00:08:08,387
[CROWD]
It's the Buggy Pirates! Ah!

160
00:08:08,421 --> 00:08:12,358
[BUGGY] You people flashily
stay where you are!

161
00:08:12,358 --> 00:08:14,360
I want every single one of you

162
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:19,365
to see exactly how
scary I can be.

163
00:08:19,365 --> 00:08:21,334
Oh yeah! Buggy, right?!

164
00:08:21,367 --> 00:08:23,870
You mean you just now
remembered it?!

165
00:08:25,438 --> 00:08:27,707
Hey! What gives?!

166
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:30,710
Long time no see,
you rubber freak.

167
00:08:30,710 --> 00:08:33,045
How's your pal Roronoa Zoro?

168
00:08:33,045 --> 00:08:35,948
[BUGGY]
Got 'em. Good job, Cabaji.

169
00:08:36,015 --> 00:08:39,752
[laughing]

170
00:08:39,785 --> 00:08:41,587
[BUGGY]
To all of my followers,

171
00:08:41,621 --> 00:08:43,956
hundreds of billions of
them around the world,

172
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:48,027
we will now super flashily
begin the public execution!

173
00:08:48,060 --> 00:08:50,062
You're trapped Monkey D. Luffy!

174
00:08:50,062 --> 00:08:52,532
You can't move so
much as an inch!

175
00:08:52,565 --> 00:08:53,566
[BUGGY laughing]

176
00:08:53,599 --> 00:08:55,601
Tell me, Straw Hat,
feel honored?

177
00:08:55,635 --> 00:08:58,571
You'll die in the same place
as the King of the Pirates!

178
00:08:58,571 --> 00:09:05,077
[laughing]

179
00:09:13,152 --> 00:09:15,621
The barometric pressure
is falling fast.

180
00:09:15,655 --> 00:09:18,491
I've never seen such
a sharp drop before.

181
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:21,761
You know, I thought
I felt something strange.

182
00:09:21,761 --> 00:09:24,597
[NAMI] There's a storm headed
straight for the island.

183
00:09:24,597 --> 00:09:26,132
[USOPP]
A storm?

184
00:09:26,165 --> 00:09:27,733
[NAMI] Yeah, we'd better
hurry back to the ship

185
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:28,668
or we'll be in trouble.

186
00:09:28,734 --> 00:09:29,902
Is it gonna be big?

187
00:09:29,936 --> 00:09:31,437
[ZORO]
Hey!

188
00:09:31,470 --> 00:09:32,438
[NAMI]
Zoro!

189
00:09:32,471 --> 00:09:34,840
Where is he? Have you
guys seen him around?

190
00:09:34,907 --> 00:09:36,609
You mean Luffy?

191
00:09:36,642 --> 00:09:40,780
[ZORO] Yeah. We got separated.
And I keep gettin' this feeling.

192
00:09:41,747 --> 00:09:42,782
It's not good.

193
00:09:42,815 --> 00:09:46,786
It usually means that something
bad's gonna happen.

194
00:09:48,154 --> 00:09:49,322
[TOWNSMAN 7 screams]

195
00:09:49,355 --> 00:09:51,190
[TOWNSMAN 8]
Pirates are here!

196
00:09:51,257 --> 00:09:52,158
[TOWNSMAN 1]
Holy crap!

197
00:09:52,191 --> 00:09:52,992
[TOWNSMAN 2]
Run!

198
00:09:53,025 --> 00:09:55,328
[TOWNSMAN 3]
It's Buggy the Clown!

199
00:09:55,361 --> 00:09:56,596
What'd they say?

200
00:09:56,629 --> 00:09:58,764
I think they said Buggy.

201
00:10:02,802 --> 00:10:05,171
[SMOKER]
Hmm. And then what?

202
00:10:05,204 --> 00:10:06,539
[GENERAL]
Well, sir,

203
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:07,840
it isn't just Straw Hat Luffy,

204
00:10:07,873 --> 00:10:10,810
it's also Buggy the Clown,
and Iron Club Alvida.

205
00:10:10,810 --> 00:10:14,146
They're all there! Wanted
pirates from the East Blue

206
00:10:14,180 --> 00:10:17,316
have taken over
our town square!

207
00:10:17,316 --> 00:10:20,720
They do all of this
right in front of me?

208
00:10:20,786 --> 00:10:23,189
Why those arrogant scumbags.

209
00:10:23,222 --> 00:10:26,792
Captain Smoker, sir,
what are your orders?

210
00:10:26,826 --> 00:10:28,828
Send unit number one
out to the sea,

211
00:10:28,861 --> 00:10:31,297
and have unit number two
surround the pirates

212
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:32,531
from the streets.

213
00:10:32,565 --> 00:10:34,834
The rest will stand by within
shooting range of the square.

214
00:10:34,867 --> 00:10:36,335
See that it's done.

215
00:10:36,369 --> 00:10:37,670
[GENERAL]
Sir!

216
00:10:37,703 --> 00:10:40,406
[SMOKER]
And give this order to unit one.

217
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:43,809
They are to crush any pirate
ships as soon as they see them.

218
00:10:43,843 --> 00:10:46,178
I don't want a single one
of those wretched pirates

219
00:10:46,212 --> 00:10:47,413
to get off this island.

220
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,682
Not a single one.

221
00:10:55,521 --> 00:10:57,189
[TOWNSMAN 5]
It's time for the execution!

222
00:10:57,223 --> 00:11:00,192
[TOWNSMAN 4] Buggy the Clown
is gonna kill Straw Hat Luffy!

223
00:11:00,226 --> 00:11:01,260
Yeah!

224
00:11:01,327 --> 00:11:03,229
They're gonna execute him?!

225
00:11:03,262 --> 00:11:04,597
That freakin' idiot!

226
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:05,598
[ZORO]
Let's go!

227
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:06,365
[SANJI]
Hold this.

228
00:11:06,365 --> 00:11:08,868
[USOPP yelping]

229
00:11:08,901 --> 00:11:10,836
[USOPP]
San‐‐ Sanji!

230
00:11:10,870 --> 00:11:14,540
[SANJI] And treat it like
a lady, you got that?!

231
00:11:14,573 --> 00:11:15,875
[NAMI]
Come on, we gotta hurry!

232
00:11:15,875 --> 00:11:17,410
[USOPP]
Where're we goin', Nami?!

233
00:11:17,443 --> 00:11:19,211
[NAMI]
The harbor, you numbskull!

234
00:11:19,245 --> 00:11:22,848
[USOPP] Harbor?
Oh yeah, I knew that!

235
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:26,552
[MARINE A]
Captain Smoker. Look!

236
00:11:26,552 --> 00:11:28,454
[MARINE B]
Things are getting weird.

237
00:11:30,589 --> 00:11:32,892
[SMOKER]
It's that kid.

238
00:11:32,892 --> 00:11:34,460
What's he doing out there?

239
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:36,562
Well, if I didn't
know any better,

240
00:11:36,562 --> 00:11:40,900
I would say that Monkey D. Luffy
is about to be executed.

241
00:11:40,933 --> 00:11:43,736
[SMOKER]
That kid looks pathetic.

242
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:49,575
Personal quest. To see where
the King of the Pirates died.

243
00:11:49,608 --> 00:11:51,911
Huh...

244
00:11:51,911 --> 00:11:55,448
[SMOKER] For some reason
that kid caught my attention.

245
00:11:55,481 --> 00:11:58,751
I thought he was different
from the others.

246
00:11:58,751 --> 00:12:03,322
Looks like he's nothing
but pirate scum after all.

247
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:05,591
Captain, we are
ready to attack.

248
00:12:05,624 --> 00:12:06,759
Don't be hasty.

249
00:12:06,759 --> 00:12:09,328
But we've got them
surrounded, sir!

250
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:12,264
I'm in command! You got it?

251
00:12:12,298 --> 00:12:13,833
Yes, sir.

252
00:12:13,899 --> 00:12:16,268
[SMOKER] One pirate is
about to kill another.

253
00:12:16,302 --> 00:12:21,307
Let them fight it out first.
That'll save us the trouble.

254
00:12:21,340 --> 00:12:24,443
Listen, once that
Straw Hat loses his head,

255
00:12:24,477 --> 00:12:27,580
we surround Buggy,
Alvida, and their gang.

256
00:12:27,613 --> 00:12:29,348
And do it fast!

257
00:12:33,419 --> 00:12:36,622
[BUGGY laughing]

258
00:12:36,622 --> 00:12:39,358
[BUGGY]
Pirate Monkey D. Luffy...

259
00:12:39,425 --> 00:12:43,796
...of the Straw Hats,
will be flashily executed..

260
00:12:43,796 --> 00:12:48,367
...for the crime of being stuck
up and making me angry!

261
00:12:48,434 --> 00:12:50,936
Now live it up flashily!

262
00:12:53,639 --> 00:12:56,342
Oh boy, I've never
seen an execution.

263
00:12:56,375 --> 00:12:58,611
Well, you're about to kid.

264
00:12:58,644 --> 00:12:59,879
[LUFFY]
Hm?

265
00:12:59,945 --> 00:13:01,814
What?! Stop joking!

266
00:13:01,814 --> 00:13:03,783
It's no joke.

267
00:13:03,816 --> 00:13:04,683
[LUFFY] Take this
board off, you bastard!

268
00:13:04,717 --> 00:13:07,853
[BUGGY] All right!
I hereby flashily begin

269
00:13:07,887 --> 00:13:11,657
the festivities of this
public execution!

270
00:13:11,690 --> 00:13:14,827
[BUGGY laughing]

271
00:13:30,543 --> 00:13:33,546
[NAMI] I saw a massive cumulus
cloud in the eastern sky!

272
00:13:33,579 --> 00:13:36,382
That means an unimaginably
big storm is headed our way.

273
00:13:36,415 --> 00:13:38,484
And it's coming in fast!

274
00:13:38,517 --> 00:13:40,052
If Buggy and Luffy
have caused a scene,

275
00:13:40,085 --> 00:13:42,721
the Marines are sure
to come out.

276
00:13:42,755 --> 00:13:45,691
And if our ship is washed out
to sea when we need to escape,

277
00:13:45,724 --> 00:13:46,692
we're done for.

278
00:13:46,692 --> 00:13:48,160
That is a big deal!

279
00:13:48,194 --> 00:13:49,261
As a matter of fact,

280
00:13:49,328 --> 00:13:52,164
I bet the Marines have already
started taking action!

281
00:13:52,198 --> 00:13:55,367
And they'll destroy the
Going Merry if they find it!

282
00:13:55,401 --> 00:13:56,435
[USOPP]
Hold on!

283
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:59,672
So you're telling me the
Going Merry's in danger?!

284
00:14:01,207 --> 00:14:03,042
[USOPP]
C'mon, Nami! Hurry up!

285
00:14:03,075 --> 00:14:05,711
[NAMI]
Wait for me!

286
00:14:05,711 --> 00:14:07,680
[UNIT LEADER]
Okay, men, double time!

287
00:14:07,713 --> 00:14:09,715
We have to get to the
harbor immediately

288
00:14:09,715 --> 00:14:11,750
and destroy every
last pirate vessel!

289
00:14:11,784 --> 00:14:13,118
[MARINES]
Yes, sir!

290
00:14:20,426 --> 00:14:22,561
[MOHJI] ♪ Riding around
on a Ritchie bike! ♪

291
00:14:22,595 --> 00:14:25,798
♪ Who's that man?
Who's that man? Who? Who? ♪

292
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:28,934
♪ Who's that man riding
around on a Ritchie bike! ♪

293
00:14:28,968 --> 00:14:33,072
Oh yes, it's me!

294
00:14:33,072 --> 00:14:36,575
So this is the rubber
guy's ship, huh?

295
00:14:36,609 --> 00:14:38,744
[RICHIE]
Uh‐huh.

296
00:14:38,744 --> 00:14:39,912
Would ya look at that?

297
00:14:39,945 --> 00:14:42,815
He's got a bigger ship. He
won't need it where he's going.

298
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:47,086
Cause it's almost time for Buggy
to flashily finish him off.

299
00:14:47,086 --> 00:14:49,154
However, just in case
the rubber guy,

300
00:14:49,221 --> 00:14:52,591
who has absolutely no chance of
escaping, happens to escape,

301
00:14:52,591 --> 00:14:54,994
we need to burn this ship down.

302
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:57,730
Burning wood smells so good.

303
00:14:57,763 --> 00:15:00,733
[grunting]

304
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:07,940
I'm so sorry. Really, I am.
Please spare my life.

305
00:15:07,940 --> 00:15:10,242
Why would I spare your life?!

306
00:15:10,276 --> 00:15:13,479
This is what happens
when you go against us.

307
00:15:13,512 --> 00:15:17,449
I guess this is it for
the man I had my eye on.

308
00:15:17,483 --> 00:15:20,619
You've got quite a big audience
here today, Straw Hat.

309
00:15:20,653 --> 00:15:24,623
You wanna say a few
words before you die?

310
00:15:24,623 --> 00:15:26,926
Oh? Cat got your tongue?

311
00:15:26,959 --> 00:15:29,662
That's all right. Stay quiet,
or say a few words,

312
00:15:29,695 --> 00:15:32,765
it doesn't matter,
you're still gonna die!

313
00:15:35,501 --> 00:15:40,873
Listen! I'm the man who'll
be King of the Pirates!

314
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:45,010
I'm the man who'll be
King of the Pirates!

315
00:15:45,044 --> 00:15:49,481
I'm the man who'll be
King of the Pirates!

316
00:15:53,552 --> 00:15:54,987
[TOWNSMAN 6]
What?

317
00:15:55,020 --> 00:15:57,790
[TOWNSMAN 7]
He said... King of the Pirates.

318
00:15:57,823 --> 00:16:00,025
[TOWNSMAN 1]
In this town of all places?

319
00:16:00,059 --> 00:16:02,161
[TOWNSMAN 2]
That's a crazy thing to say.

320
00:16:06,131 --> 00:16:09,001
We're finally getting to
the best part of the show.

321
00:16:09,034 --> 00:16:10,469
Bye, bye now.

322
00:16:12,571 --> 00:16:13,539
[chuckles]

323
00:16:13,572 --> 00:16:15,975
[ZORO]
Stop the execution!

324
00:16:16,008 --> 00:16:17,409
[ZORO, SANJI]
Now!

325
00:16:21,413 --> 00:16:24,083
Sanji! Zoro!

326
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:26,218
Zoro!

327
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:30,055
Luffy, you idiot.

328
00:16:30,089 --> 00:16:33,492
Guess all that foolin' around
finally caught up with ya, huh?

329
00:16:33,492 --> 00:16:35,394
[SANJI]
You startin' a sideshow?

330
00:16:35,427 --> 00:16:38,664
Or is that just how
you look? Pretty sad.

331
00:16:38,664 --> 00:16:42,034
Now what we gotta do is
drive these goons away.

332
00:16:42,067 --> 00:16:44,903
[TOWNSMAN 1]
N‐No! It's pirate hunter Zoro!

333
00:16:44,937 --> 00:16:47,239
[CROWD screaming]

334
00:16:47,272 --> 00:16:49,174
Hey, guys! Heh!

335
00:16:49,174 --> 00:16:53,278
You made it, Zoro! But you're
just a little bit too late.

336
00:16:55,047 --> 00:16:57,516
[ZORO] We gotta bring
down the platform

337
00:16:57,516 --> 00:16:59,918
Roronoa... Zoro.

338
00:17:01,954 --> 00:17:03,689
Okay, boys! Get 'em!

339
00:17:03,722 --> 00:17:05,524
[PIRATE A]
Let's do it!

340
00:17:05,557 --> 00:17:07,359
[PIRATE B]
Yeah!

341
00:17:11,964 --> 00:17:13,365
[ZORO]
Outta our way!

342
00:17:18,637 --> 00:17:20,973
[laughing]

343
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:23,709
Not even the great Zoro
can stop me now!

344
00:17:23,742 --> 00:17:25,577
There's nothing you two can do!

345
00:17:25,611 --> 00:17:28,414
It's the end for your captain!

346
00:17:28,447 --> 00:17:29,715
Bastard!

347
00:17:33,218 --> 00:17:36,388
[ZORO] If I can just cut
down the platform...

348
00:17:36,422 --> 00:17:37,322
[MARINE C]
Listen.

349
00:17:37,389 --> 00:17:39,658
The moment Monkey D.
Luffy's head falls,

350
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:42,227
we all attack together.

351
00:17:44,329 --> 00:17:45,731
Prepare for battle.

352
00:17:45,764 --> 00:17:46,565
[MARINES]
Sir!

353
00:17:46,598 --> 00:17:53,072
[BUGGY laughing]

354
00:17:53,105 --> 00:17:55,074
[LUFFY]
Zoro! Sanji!

355
00:17:55,107 --> 00:17:57,576
Usopp! Nami!

356
00:17:57,576 --> 00:17:59,078
Sorry.

357
00:18:00,245 --> 00:18:03,182
[LUFFY]
But... I'm dead.

358
00:18:05,584 --> 00:18:07,586
[ZORO]
Idiot!

359
00:18:07,586 --> 00:18:09,521
[SANJI]
Don't say that!

360
00:18:09,588 --> 00:18:11,590
He smiled.

361
00:19:20,526 --> 00:19:22,394
[laughing]

362
00:19:22,427 --> 00:19:26,165
I'm still alive! That's nice!

363
00:19:31,537 --> 00:19:33,772
That was divine intervention.

364
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:37,843
[ZORO] Stop talkin' nonsense.
We gotta get outta this town.

365
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:39,511
Our troubles are not over.

366
00:19:39,511 --> 00:19:41,180
[LUFFY laughing]

367
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:47,553
Attack! Surround all
the pirates now!

368
00:19:47,586 --> 00:19:51,623
[MARINES yelling]

369
00:19:51,690 --> 00:19:53,392
[SANJI]
Here they come!

370
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:02,467
Oh wow! So cool!

371
00:20:02,534 --> 00:20:05,237
Everybody here went
crazy so quickly.

372
00:20:05,270 --> 00:20:05,737
[ZORO]
Luffy!

373
00:20:05,771 --> 00:20:07,573
[LUFFY screaming]

374
00:20:07,606 --> 00:20:08,807
Zoro!

375
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:10,776
We don't have time for this.
We have got to get outta here.

376
00:20:10,809 --> 00:20:12,711
We'd better hurry back
to the Going Merry

377
00:20:12,711 --> 00:20:15,147
or we'll never be able
to leave this island.

378
00:20:15,214 --> 00:20:17,216
And we sure as hell
won't get to the Grand Line!

379
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:20,886
Really? Well,
that's no good. Run!

380
00:20:20,919 --> 00:20:24,289
The Straw Hat Gang
is getting away!

381
00:20:24,323 --> 00:20:26,091
[MARINE C]
Capture them!

382
00:20:30,395 --> 00:20:32,731
[SMOKER]
Why did he smile?

383
00:20:32,764 --> 00:20:36,401
Did he know he'd be saved?

384
00:20:36,401 --> 00:20:37,636
No.

385
00:20:37,669 --> 00:20:42,507
At that moment, he was certain
that his life was about to end.

386
00:20:42,574 --> 00:20:44,176
He simply accepted death,

387
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:46,812
and smiled after
preparing himself.

388
00:20:46,845 --> 00:20:49,748
Captain, we have to
pursue the pirates.

389
00:20:51,316 --> 00:20:53,485
Lieutenant, think back.

390
00:20:53,518 --> 00:20:55,621
Have you ever seen
any pirates who smiled

391
00:20:55,654 --> 00:20:58,924
on the execution platform?

392
00:20:58,924 --> 00:20:59,825
[LT. COMMANDER]
No, sir.

393
00:20:59,858 --> 00:21:01,793
It doesn't matter how
tough the guy is.

394
00:21:01,827 --> 00:21:05,764
At the moment of death, they all
turn pale and die in despair.

395
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:10,469
[SMOKER] That Straw Hat
man smiled. I saw it.

396
00:21:10,502 --> 00:21:14,339
He smiled just like
Gold Roger, 22 years ago.

397
00:21:14,373 --> 00:21:17,209
Just like the old King
of the Pirates did

398
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:20,345
on that exact
execution platform.

399
00:21:29,621 --> 00:21:31,823
Captain.

400
00:21:31,857 --> 00:21:33,659
Where's the Straw Hat man now?

401
00:21:33,692 --> 00:21:34,826
Sir.

402
00:21:34,860 --> 00:21:37,496
He slipped past us and is
heading towards the harbor.

403
00:21:40,299 --> 00:21:42,734
[SMOKER] Unit one should've
destroyed their ship by now.

404
00:21:42,801 --> 00:21:45,971
Well, sir. They had to return
to port for a refitting.

405
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:49,408
See, they couldn't light their
powder due to the sudden rain.

406
00:21:49,474 --> 00:21:51,209
[SMOKER]
What?!

407
00:21:51,243 --> 00:21:52,477
But a reserve unit

408
00:21:52,477 --> 00:21:55,314
is currently making preparations
to attack the ship instead.

409
00:21:55,347 --> 00:21:57,382
Captain Smoker,
if we let them sail now,

410
00:21:57,416 --> 00:21:58,984
they'll be able to
get to the Grand Line

411
00:21:59,017 --> 00:22:01,687
before we can capture them.

412
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:04,589
[SMOKER] The wind is blowing
towards the west.

413
00:22:04,656 --> 00:22:07,326
It's a tailwind for that ship.

414
00:22:09,661 --> 00:22:12,497
[SMOKER]
Is this just mere coincidence?

415
00:22:13,932 --> 00:22:16,335
It's as if heaven itself
has special plans

416
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:18,904
for this young pirate.

417
00:22:18,937 --> 00:22:22,007
[ZORO] We'd better pick up
the pace or we're toast!

418
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:24,376
[SMOKER]
I am White Hunter Smoker.

419
00:22:24,409 --> 00:22:26,912
On my honor as Marine Captain,

420
00:22:26,945 --> 00:22:31,450
I won't let that man
leave this island!

421
00:22:51,303 --> 00:22:57,776
[MAN] Blow, winds!
The storm of fate has arrived!

422
00:23:03,949 --> 00:23:06,718
<i>♪All that's in my</i>
<i>heart confuses me,</i>

423
00:23:06,718 --> 00:23:08,820
<i>I cannot understand,</i>

424
00:23:08,887 --> 00:23:10,889
<i>As I face what I must do,</i>

425
00:23:10,889 --> 00:23:13,792
<i>I'll say goodbye</i>
<i>and squeeze your hand.</i>

426
00:23:13,825 --> 00:23:15,394
<i>I'll set sail alone,</i>

427
00:23:15,427 --> 00:23:18,730
<i>But always know</i>
<i>I'm gonna keep you near,</i>

428
00:23:18,730 --> 00:23:20,399
<i>As I drift away,</i>

429
00:23:20,399 --> 00:23:24,336
<i>I pray you watch me</i>
<i>as I disappear.</i>

430
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:33,578
<i>As I watch the sunrise,</i>
<i>I began to wonder,</i>

431
00:23:33,612 --> 00:23:38,316
<i>What could be the reason,</i>
<i>It's so hot inside.</i>

432
00:23:38,350 --> 00:23:40,652
<i>No answer has come,</i>

433
00:23:40,685 --> 00:23:44,689
<i>But I can't get away</i>
<i>from what's true,</i>

434
00:23:44,756 --> 00:23:49,528
<i>It's because of you...</i>

435
00:23:49,594 --> 00:23:51,997
<i>Show me how to</i>
<i>catch those feelings,</i>

436
00:23:52,030 --> 00:23:54,533
<i>Get 'em to come back to me,</i>

437
00:23:54,599 --> 00:23:55,967
<i>I'll do what I must,</i>

438
00:23:56,001 --> 00:23:59,504
<i>Because they're</i>
<i>everything I wanna be.</i>

439
00:23:59,538 --> 00:24:01,506
<i>Wrap these arms around my dreams</i>

440
00:24:01,540 --> 00:24:04,443
<i>And pull 'em back</i>
<i>from yesterday,</i>

441
00:24:04,476 --> 00:24:06,445
<i>If I'm holding hands with you,</i>

442
00:24:06,478 --> 00:24:09,815
<i>I'm sure that we</i>
<i>can make the way.♪</i>

